*** This is a programing language Perfume and Pmacs text editor binary package ***

<<< Package description >>>

1. Package name: pmacs-install-YYYYMMDD-amd64-ubuntu22.tar.gz
   This package for Linux distribution Ubuntu-22.04TLS, arch x86_64(AMD64).

2. Package name: pmacs-install-YYYYMMDD-amd64-redhat9.tar.gz
   This package for Linux distribution Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8, arch x86_64(AMD64).

3. Package name: pmacs-install-YYYYMMDD-amd64-freebsd.tar.gz
   This package for FreeBSD, arch x86_64(AMD64).


<<< INSTALL Perfume/Pmacs package >>>

1. Extract downloaded binary package in any directory you want to install.

        (ex) If you install into your home directory.

        cd $HOME
        tar xvzf pmacs-install-YYYYMMDD-amd64-OSTYPE.tar.gz	[ Specify package name you downloaded ]

2. Enter package directory.

        cd pmacs-install

3. Run installer.

        sh ./install.sh

4. Set the shell environment variable PATH.

        (ex) Edit your shell profile.

        PATH=${PATH}:${HOME}/bin

5. Create pmacs command file under your program path.

        (ex) Create program file in your $HOME/bin directory.

        cd $HOME/bin
        ln -s ../pmacs-install/bin/pmacs pmacs

6. Start pmacs editor.

        pmacs


#eof
